Cord leader Raila Odinga is causing anxiety among citizens by threatening to call for mass action over the Election Laws (Amendment) Bill, Kigumo MP Jamleck Kamau has said.It reminds Kenyans of the 2007-08 post-election violence following the disputed 2007 election, he said.The violence followed similar calls for mass action by Raila and Kenyans were incited to kill each other, Kamau said.Cord leaders have accused President Uhuru Kenyatta of planning to rig the election by pushing through provisions for a manual back-up system for voters identification and results transmission.They threatened mass action on January 4, but suspended their plans to give the Senate room to conclude their deliberations.The Senate passed the Bill on Thursday last week.